Eastern Cape has the third most cases countrywide. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Over 1,000 new hospital beds will be made available to fight COVID-19 in the Eastern Cape. Hospitals in the province are struggling to cope as the number of COVID-19 infections continues to climb. Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane says the virus continues to inflict pain on the people of the Eastern Cape. READ: Eastern Cape COVID-19 death toll climbs to 871 "We have completed 22 infrastructure refurbishment projects across the five districts and the other two metros," Mabuyane said. The province has over 65,000 COVID-19 cases with nearly 900 deaths. Mabuyane has said the healthcare system is still under severe pressure. The province has the third most cases countrywide. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.